  "text": "The predicted protein for Bradi2g60520 shows no similarity to any known domain or protein and it is a potential annotation error. Bradi2g60530 predicted protein includes a serine/threonine kinase, a domain involved in signal transduction in many disease resistance responses. However, serine/threonine kinases involved in disease resistance usually belong to a subclass designated as non-RD kinases, which lack the lysine (R) preceding the invariant aspartate (D) in the catalytic loop [CITATION_1] . Bradi2g60530 is an RD kinase and, therefore, is less likely to be involved in the Sr35 hypersensitive response than if it would have been a non-RD kinase.",
